    {
      "title": "ElizaOS Daily Summary: June 3, 2026",
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "Development on June 3, 2026 centered on four main areas: cloud authentication stability, UI improvements, CI/CD alignment, and ecosystem expansion. On the authentication front, the team resolved magic-link sign-in failures on the staging environment by updating CSP, CORS, and app-auth context handling across multiple pull requests. For UI and documentation, a new prompt-suggestion strip was added to the ContinuousChatOverlay to improve user onboarding, and Storybook documentation was expanded to cover nine core UI primitives, enhancing the developer experience. System stability efforts included aligning smoke tests and workspace dependencies for consistency across Bun and Vite canary builds, as well as adding typed error signaling for missing native bindings to improve local inference reliability. The ecosystem was expanded by integrating the @1claw/plugin-elizaos plugin into the curated registry, bringing support for HSM-backed secrets and multi-chain signing. Work in progress includes a cloud SSO pairing handler for a dashboard popup flow and syncing the Odysseus UI to the latest upstream changes in the plugin-task-coordinator.",
